{meta: artist Jim Reeves}
{meta: writer Jim Reeves and Al Courtney}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]If all of the stars were a [C]million [G]guitars
[D7]And the moon was the girl that I [G]loved
[C]If they played for me and to each [G]melody
[D7]We could dance in the heavens [G]above
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]If all of my wishes turned out to be [G]kisses
[D7]From an angels sweet face full of [G]charm
[C]Make believe this real then you’ll know how I [G]feel
[D7]When I’m waltzing with you in my [G]arms
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Waltzing with my darling
[C]In a paradise with my [G]girl
[C]The moment I found you my heart left the [G]ground
[D7]To go waltzing on top of the [G]world
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]If all of the stars should lay down their [G]guitars
[D7]That never would mean we should [G]pause
[C]The man in the moon might catch on to this [G]tune
[D7]And play our love song while we [G]waltz
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[C]We'd go right on dancing and find sweet [G]romancing
[D7]Then when we'd linger to [G]love
[C]My darling how sweet you'd look swinging your [G]feet
[D7]From a silver lined cloud high [G]above
{end_of_verse}

